---
import { transportModes } from "../data/setup";
---

<section class="security-summary section" aria-labelledby="security-summary-title">
	<div class="container">
		<div class="section-heading section-heading--split">
			<div>
				<p class="context-line">Credential clarity</p>
				<h2 id="security-summary-title">Know how your key is handled before you connect.</h2>
			</div>
			<p>Each method has a different credential boundary. Choose with the behavior visible.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="security-summary__modes">
			{transportModes.map((mode) => <article><h3>{mode.label}</h3><p>{mode.security}</p></article>)}
		</div>
		<p class="security-summary__mutation">Hevy MCP exposes read tools and create/update tools. Compatible clients can ask for confirmation before a mutation runs; review inputs before approving.</p>
		<a class="text-link" href="/security/">Read the security details <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
	</div>
</section>
